    <h2>What Is UNO No Mercy?</h2>
    <p>UNO No Mercy is the famously ruthless twist on classic UNO: draw penalties stack into monster piles, special wild cards wreak havoc, and instead of the round ending when someone wins, players are <strong>eliminated when their hand hits 25 cards</strong>. The last player standing takes the game. It went viral for a reason — games swing wildly, nobody is ever safe, and friendships are tested.</p>
    <p>Our free browser version brings the No Mercy experience online: no download, no app, no signup. Open the site, create a room, switch the mode to <strong>💀 No Mercy</strong>, and share the invite link.</p>

    <h2>No Mercy Rules in Our Game</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Full stacking, always on</strong> — +2 on +2, +4 on +4, and even +2s and +4s on each other. Piles keep growing until someone eats every card. <a href="/rules/stacking">How stacking works →</a></li>
      <li><strong>💥 Wild +8 cards</strong> — two per deck. Like a Wild +4, but twice as evil — and stackable.</li>
      <li><strong>🔀 Wild Shuffle Hands</strong> — everyone's cards are collected, shuffled together, and dealt back out. Your beautiful hand? Gone.</li>
      <li><strong>⚔️ Wild Challenge</strong> — think that +4 was played illegally? Challenge it. If you're right, they draw 4. If you're wrong, you draw 6.</li>
      <li><strong>🪦 Elimination at 25 cards</strong> — collect 25 cards and you're OUT. Your cards go back to the deck and the survivors play on.</li>
      <li><strong>👑 Last player standing wins</strong> — or be the first to empty your hand. Either escape route works.</li>
      <li><strong>Optional extras</strong> — the host can also enable Skip Dodge (deflect a draw pile with a Skip), Reverse Bounce (send the pile back where it came from), and the Seven-Zero hand-swap rule.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to Start a No Mercy Game</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Create a room</strong> — go to the <a href="/play">Play page</a>, enter a nickname, and create a room. It's free and takes seconds.</li>
      <li><strong>Pick 💀 No Mercy</strong> — in the room settings, tap the No Mercy mode card. The brutal rules switch on automatically.</li>
      <li><strong>Invite players (or bots)</strong> — share the invite link on WhatsApp or Discord, or add bots and start immediately. Up to 20 players per room.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>No Mercy vs Classic UNO</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Classic:</strong> first player to empty their hand wins, draw penalties resolve immediately, no stacking.</li>
      <li><strong>No Mercy:</strong> penalties stack without limit, extra wild cards poison the deck, and you can lose by drowning in cards long before anyone goes out.</li>
      <li><strong>Game feel:</strong> Classic is quick and fair. No Mercy is longer, louder, and personal. Both are free here — switch modes any time between rounds.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h3>Is UNO No Mercy free to play online?</h3>
    <p>Yes — completely free, forever. No download, no signup, no ads mid-game. It runs in any browser on phone, tablet, or computer.</p>
    <h3>How many players can join a No Mercy game?</h3>
    <p>2 to 20 players in one room. Big tables are where No Mercy really shines — more players means more stacking chains and more eliminations.</p>
    <h3>What happens when a player is eliminated?</h3>
    <p>At 25 cards they're out: their cards return to the deck and they watch the rest of the round. They're back in automatically when the next round starts.</p>
    <h3>Can I play No Mercy with bots?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Add bots from the room lobby — they stack, challenge, and get eliminated just like humans.</p>
    <h3>Is this the official Mattel game?</h3>
    <p>No. Play UNO Free is an independent, fan-made browser game inspired by the No Mercy style of play. UNO® is a registered trademark of Mattel, Inc., and we're not affiliated with them.</p>

